        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 4:35PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 435 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an line of strong winds
ahead of an area of strong thunderstorms extending from 19 miles
northwest of Ute Lake State Park to near Montoya, moving southeast
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tucumcari, Logan, Ute Lake State Park and Montoya.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 306 and 343.
State Road 104 between Mile Markers 78 and 105.

This includes the following recreation areas...
Ute Lake State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
